CI/CD PIPELINE FOR A MAVEN-BASED JAVA APPLICATION USING GIT/GITHUB, JENKINS, DOCKER AND DOCKER SWARM WITH CRON TRIGGER

STEP 1: Create Maven Project

• Open IntelliJ IDEA.
• Create a Maven Project.
• Project Name: java-swarm-app

Build the project:

mvn clean package

Expected Output:

BUILD SUCCESS

A JAR file is generated inside:

target/

------------------------------------------------------------

STEP 2: Create Dockerfile

Create a file named Dockerfile.

Paste:

FROM eclipse-temurin:17-jdk

WORKDIR /app

COPY target/*.jar app.jar

CMD ["java","-jar","app.jar"]

------------------------------------------------------------

STEP 3: Build Docker Image

Execute:

docker build -t java-swarm-app .

Check image:

docker images

Run the container:

docker run java-swarm-app

------------------------------------------------------------

STEP 4: Push Project to GitHub

Initialize Git:

git init

Add files:

git add .

Commit:

git commit -m "Initial Commit"

Connect GitHub Repository:

git remote add origin https://github.com/username/java-swarm-app.git

Push:

git push -u origin main

------------------------------------------------------------

STEP 5: Create Jenkins Pipeline

Open Jenkins:

http://localhost:8080

Create New Item

Select:

Pipeline

Configure:

Pipeline script from SCM

SCM:

Git

Repository URL:

https://github.com/username/java-swarm-app.git

Branch:

main

Script Path:

Jenkinsfile

------------------------------------------------------------

STEP 6: Configure Cron Trigger

Open the Jenkins Pipeline Job.

Click Configure.

Under Build Triggers, enable:

Build periodically

Enter the cron schedule:

* * * * *

(This runs the pipeline every minute for demonstration.)

Click Save.

------------------------------------------------------------

STEP 7: Create Jenkinsfile

Create a file named Jenkinsfile.

Paste:

pipeline {

    agent any

    stages {

        stage('Clone') {
            steps {
                checkout scm
            }
        }

        stage('Build') {
            steps {
                sh 'mvn clean package'
            }
        }

        stage('Docker Build') {
            steps {
                sh 'docker build -t java-swarm-app .'
            }
        }

        stage('Deploy to Docker Swarm') {
            steps {
                sh 'docker service create --name java-service java-swarm-app || true'
            }
        }

    }

}

Push the Jenkinsfile:

git add .

git commit -m "Added Jenkinsfile"

git push

------------------------------------------------------------

STEP 8: Initialize Docker Swarm

Execute:

docker swarm init

Verify:

docker info

Expected Output:

Swarm: active

------------------------------------------------------------

STEP 9: Execute Jenkins Pipeline

The pipeline starts automatically according to the cron schedule.

Or click:

Build Now

Pipeline Stages:

Stage 1:
Clone Repository

Stage 2:
Build Maven Project

Stage 3:
Build Docker Image

Stage 4:
Deploy Docker Service

Finished: SUCCESS

------------------------------------------------------------

STEP 10: Verify Deployment

Check Swarm Services:

docker service ls

Check Running Containers:

docker ps

Check Service Logs:

docker service logs java-service

------------------------------------------------------------

STEP 11: Remove Service

docker service rm java-service

